Also, I read a lot of reviews complaining about the charging port protection and how they are unable to put their cable into the charging port but... either you're doing it blind or using the wrong type of charger cause I have had absolutely zero issues with that and nobody should have ANY type of difficulty and problem with that. Anyway, I feel like I've said enough. I know the price is on the steeper side but it's better to get a quality case than a cheap one and having to buy multiple throughout the year(s).

product: TAURI for iPhone 14 Pro Max Phone Case, [5 in 1] 1X Clear Case [Not-Yellowing] with 2X Tempered Glass Screen Protector + 2X Camera Lens Protector, [Military-Grade Drop Protection] Phone Case 6.7 Inch
title: If you're as anal as I am, you are going to want to read this.
body: First off, I have to say this is the ultimate screen protector, camera lens protector, and overall body impact protector. Why? Let me explain.I had a lot of reservations first when it came to mounting this on my iPhone 14 Pro Max. For one I didn't want anything plastic getting in the way of the phenomenal video, and photo taking capabilities. I know high quality You Tube channels and this phone is all they use. Well guess what? The lens cover is made from solid glass. That's right, they even give you the alcohol wipes, and dust collector... more about that in a minute.The clear plastic (in my case) thicker housing protector is designed to give you protection for up to a 10-foot drop. Nothing can be more devastating than to have such a serious investment, into a seriously high-quality instrument only to crash it to the ground.Now let‚Äôs talk about the display clear plastic cover, which is the reason I came to write this review in the first place. Let me first say there are elaborate installation instructions for this specific case on You Tube, and yes, a picture does say a thousand words; just look up " iPhone 14 Series - Installation Video [with Alignment Frame] " for a step by step, hand holding guide. Okay it is a straightforward guide.Here is the one tip I want to provide which to me is crucial, and wish I knew it ahead of time. After you are done wiping down the phone large screen with the included alcohol wipe, and then drying it off with the included microfiber cloth, BE SURE to use the sticky dust collector and do it multiple times. I thought I was being very particular not to miss a spot, but one tiny dust spec stayed behind, and when you are installing it, using the rectangular installation guide that is included, once it goes on, you are not going to get it off very easily. In plain words, in order to remove it, you will need to buy another kit to put one back on. Mine had that one spec. You may think, what the heck only a spec, but the problem is the whole screen protector just flows on (see the video) but that one spec will create an every so tiny mountain around the spec. In plain words you will see a very small air space around that spec that you can't smush down; you have to learn to live with it. I know this is being overly critical, but it is very simple to avoid; don't scrimp on using the sticky dust collector piece they include with it, go over it again, and again.,Okay it is definitely a great piece of mind knowing how well this protector works. First off, the screen protector works without slowing down the efficiency of the device, or should I say the sensitivity of the phone to your finger touch "instruction", you know, swipe, tap etc. Then the drop protection is paramount, and finally, knowing you have real glass stick on around the circumference of the lens area means there is not reduction in the mind-blowing quality of videos, and photos this phone takes. For crying out loud, I am getting 4K at 60fps out of a cell phone. Even though I have an array of cameras including a Canon R7, and a DJI Osmo Action camera, this is the one that is always with you, and takes photos, and sports image stabilization that is on a par with them, and it is even easier to use with the fabulous presets. Highly, highly recommended.

title: Hard drop on hard tile, camera down ‚Äì not a scratch.
body: Since I got this case, I've been a tiny bit concerned about whether the beveled part around the camera was high enough to truly protect it. I've been shopping around for camera protectors to put on in addition to the case, but haven't found one yet.Well last night, I dropped that sucker on a bathroom floor with super hard tile, camera side down. It landed completely flat, and was so loud. Lo and behold, not a single scratch. Not even on case itself. I also took a few photos in various lighting afterward to see if there was any internal damage to the camera, and didn't see anything.I've only had it for about 10 days, so I can't report about any yellowing, but I've had a couple of mediocre drops on the corners, and then this big drop on the back of the phone, and it's definitely done its job. At a fraction of the price of higher brand cases (mine was half off when I bought it), it's definitely worth your money, even if you have to buy a couple over the phone's lifetime.Lastly, in case anyone is wondering, I'm using the Otterbox trusted glass screen protector, and this case fits wonderfully with it. Highly recommend both!

title: Bubbles under screen protector
body: Very strong and seemingly durable Hard Case for my iPhone 12. The only problem I have (I've only had it for a day so we'll see what else, if anything, comes up) is that the little pieces of adhesive plastc Screen Protectors/Covers (i think 3 came w/it which is nice) do indeed "bubble up" after being put on. I tried multiple times to put em on with out any "bubbling" underneath but each time was just as bad as the last. Perhaps using a very timely procedure and a small flat edged plastic "putty or wallpaper scrapping/pushing" type tool used from top to bottom to get all air the out while applying the Protector sheet of plastic making sure to "push" the air out using this little tool I'm imagining then maybe that would work. Maybe... Other than that, great Hard Case, great fit, a bit of a smoother texture but still has grip, comes in a variety of colors, and is worth whatever I paid for it. I say that because I think I got it on sale and saved some money. So there ya go. I also have another Soft Case that seems very good too and also worth the money but this one is seemingly more durable, tougher. We'll see what happens in the future. Fingers crossed.  Thanks for reading. All the best.

The case is easy to install, and a nice clear case so that I can see the awesome Deep Purple color of the phone itself. This case kit costs about half of what other cases cost that are similar, and way less than the official Apple case. You really can't go wrong with this case. Well done!Edit:  Adding the note that this DOES work with the wireless charger. It has to be a MagSafe charger, but I bought a MagSafe compatible wireless charger and it works perfectly fine with this case.

title: Very nice case, similar to eLago
body: This is a very nice case, especially at this price point, and I would recommend it.  However, it is nearly identical to the eLago and I liked that one slightly more:https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B08G8L876Z/This case feels wonderful in the hand, like soft velvet, but because it's silicone it is also not slippery and easy to keep a grip on.  The holes all line up well, but my slightly larger than official Apple Lightning adapter doesn't quite fit in the hole, but the case accommodates this pretty easily by easily bending up when the cable is inserted (eLago hole is bigger and doesn't have this minor issue).  On this case versus the eLago, I think the OUXUL has slightly better support for the button covers.  The eLago however has slightly better reinforcement along the long sides of the phone.This case and the eLago both are a bit difficult to remove from the pocket while sitting, so if that's something you want than you may want to consider something different.  I however like this because this case and the eLago don't let the phone fall out of my pocket while sitting in my recliners like most other cases do.So I do recommend this case, but for me the eLago was ever so slightly better.  For you, this case could be better than the eLago.  They are however very similar and until really looking at the two deeply I thought they were actually identical.

title: Disappointed, it yellows
body: So the case is guaranteed it doesn‚Äôt yellow but it does. I had this case for exactly 1 month and u can tell it‚Äôs yellowing. It doesn‚Äôt yellow as fast as the $1-$2 case you get on shein  but it definitely yellows way too quickly for the price. What I was most disappointed with was the dust. I clean my phone pretty often. I clean the screen once or twice a day and deep clean the back of the phone, case , camera, screen once every 2-3 days. By the third day the back of the phone has so much dust it‚Äôs ridiculous. I don‚Äôt put my phone in dusty places, I don‚Äôt put it in my pants and I often clean it with a micro fiber cloth. I never had this issue with other cases. Yet dust can get trapped into the back of the case. The last issue is water marks. There always seem to have some liquid trapped at the back of the case. My phoen doesn‚Äôt over heat because I play games on my old phone to prevent the battery from wearing on this phone. I do not charge my phone over night. I don‚Äôt know why there‚Äôs water stain at the back of the case, it can be 20 mins after I cleaned the case and let the case dry, wipe it down, etc and there will be water there. I gotten other clear protective cases on Amazon for my iPhone 12 Pro Max and there‚Äôs never water stains in the back. That phone also overheats from playing games and nothing. My iPhone X also over heats and the clear cases never has water stains in the back. Not worth the $22+ tax I had to pay for this case. The guarantee rly disappointed me and I usually hate complaining but I genuinely am very upset with the many issues. If you are reading this I would say trust me and try another company and save your self the time unless u don‚Äôt mind these issues. As I am typing this. I just deep clean my phone around 30 mins ago. There‚Äôs already hella dust on the back trapped in between the case and the phone. They are very hard to get out too. This phone also gets oily rly fast for some reason. Just the case. The screen is fine. Like I said there isn‚Äôt issues like this on my other phone. I can‚Äôt seem to find the brand I use to use since it‚Äôs been awhile but if I do find it I‚Äôll definitely try that on the 13 pro max. I don‚Äôt have any other issues other than fingerprint even tho it‚Äôs says ‚Äúfingerprint proof‚Äù it‚Äôs a clear case so I understand that.

The main good point is unless a truck were to run over this case it's safe to say I feel comfortable not worrying about dropping this phone. My 2 negatives about the case are, 1 the spen in the holder is super hard to get out once it's placed in the holder snug. I have to use something to help me remove the spen out of holder almost every time i go to take the pen out. My biggest drawback is you can't lay this phone flat to type or write. The only way to write is to hold the phone in your hand. Not to mention but when you open the phone up the spen holder doesn't close it stays open and that to me is a terrible design flaw. So I gave it a 4 star rating only because an expensive phone should have an expensive case to protect it i guess. To be honest I feel like I should return it but what else is out there to not only protect phone and carry spen at the same time. Samsung should wake up and realize if your going to make 2 premium phones with an spen,then make them both with the spen built in.

title: Water entered after 10 minutes in the water
body: I recently purchased this iPhone 14 Pro case that claimed to be IP68 water-proof from Amazon. I was excited to try it out on my recent trip to Ginnie Springs in Florida, but my experience was extremely disappointing. After using it for less than ten minutes, I noticed two water drops when I opened the case.Before using the case with my phone, I tested it thoroughly and made sure that it was fully closed. However, despite these precautions, the case failed to keep my phone dry. I was initially impressed with the durable build of the case, but my excitement quickly turned to frustration after my experience in the water.As someone who values the safety and protection of my phone, I will never risk using this case again. I recently purchased a new phone and cannot afford to take any chances with its safety. It was such a waste of money to purchase a case that I only used for 10 minutes, and I didn't even go deep enough in the water for it to be truly tested.Overall, I would not recommend this case to anyone looking for a reliable and effective water-proof solution for their iPhone. It simply does not deliver the results it promises and is not worth the risk of damaging your phone.

product: Humixx Ultra Clear for Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra Case, [Never Yellow] [Mil-Grade Shockproof Protection] 2X Flexible Screen Protector + 2X Camera Protector Soft Slim Transparent Protective Case 6.8‚Äù
title: Great looking case. Just lacking one feature.
body: This is a great-looking case. I love the metallic green color. It fits very snugly on my Samsung Galaxy s23 Ultra. The cutouts for the microphone, S-pen, speaker, and USB ports are well done and line up perfectly. The only thing I did not like about the case is that it is very slick and slippery. I would have preferred that there be some grippiness to the case. Maybe some ridges on the side would make it feel more secure in your hands.The kit includes two screen protectors and 2 camera lens protectors. The screen protector is installed very easily using the guide attachment. Just plug the guide attachment into the USB port and sit the guide holes on the protector onto the guide. This allows you to line up the screen protector precisely. Once the screen protector is lined up, remove the backing and smooth the protector in place using the included tool. Make sure you get the edges as well. The adhesion is excellent and there was minimal bubbling which was easily massaged out using the included tool. There is a video to watch which shows you how to install the screen protector. The lens protector fits right over the lens. Be careful not to touch the lens with the adhesive on the edges. Lastly, pop the phone into the case.Edit: I was contacted by customer support and they worked with me to make sure I was completely satisfied. They took my comments back to manufacturing and even offered me a replacement case that had a better grip. Great job on the after-purchase customer support. 5 stars!

product: Apple iPhone 12 and iPhone 12 Pro Silicone Case with MagSafe - Black
title: Magnet is weak, and that was the only reason to pay $50 for a plastic case
body: Got this at the Apple Store for my iPhone 12 Pro. I've never bothered with Apple's silicone cases before because they are massively overpriced considering there's reputable quality brands with better cases for the iPhone for about 1/3 the cost. And for 1/3 the cost you get far, far more protection. If I'm going to shell out $50, at least make it the leather case which they didn't even offer for the 12's. So the only reason to even consider this case was the promised MagSafe magnet integrated into the case, allegedly. I have zero interest in their wireless MagSafe charger because it charges far slower than a USC-C cable with an 18W or 20W charger anyway, so what's the point? But I do use a magnet-based connection for my phone in the car, so I figured it could serve that purpose. The problem is the magnet in the phone and the case is so weak as to be useless for probably anything beyond helping hold the wireless charger loosely in place. The phone falls right off. For $9 on Amazon you can get 2 car connectors and 4 magnets to place inside your phone case behind your phone. And those magnet are about 10x stronger than this one. Mine works great even with the thicker Apple leather case for the 11's, or other third party cases -- nice secure hold. So basically you are paying $45 more than comparable plastic covers for a $0.10 integrated magnet too weak for most purposes. The case also isn't very snug so not a lot of confidence it will really hold the phone in a fall. Combined with no real border protection I'm not sure what this case is supposed to accomplish.

product: SUPCASE Unicorn Beetle Pro Case for Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 5G (2022), Full-Body Dual Layer Rugged Case with Built-in Screen Protector & Kickstand & S Pen Slot (Black)
title: Hefty and the feel of protection
body: I've used this for two days now and really like the protection and features. I bought the Samsung Fold 4 case with S pen when I bought the phone, but it had too little protection from drops. I've dropped phones before, and I expect that I'll drop my Fold 4 someday, too. The Supcase Unicorn Beetle Pro has soft corners to cushion any drops. The built-in front screen protector is a nice touch. The left side of the case protecting the front screen covers about 0.5 mm of the screen. No big deal. The one negative that I'll point out concerns the removable, plastic layer over the front screen protector (it ships with the removable plastic layer for protection). When I removed it, it left behind some residue on the backside of the screen protector. I had to use Goo Gone (Goof Off) to remove it. The S Pen holder doubles as protection for the hinge, a very important feature. Note that the case can only hold the 5.31" long S pen Fold edition. It will NOT hold the 6.73" long S Pen Pro. Another feature that I like over the Samsung Fold S Pen Case is that the Supcase lies flat when you are using the front screen. The built-in stand works well for using the Fold 4 with the front screen and opened with the full screen. Some people have complained that the S Pen holder does not close by itself. That doesn't bother me. It closes with a satisfying click. The camera lenses are now recessed, too. I love the feel of the case in my hand. It doesn't feel as if it would slip out of my grasp at all. Yes, it makes the already bulky Fold 4 slightly more bulky; but if you bought a Fold 4, bulkiness is not your concern anyway.**UPDATE** After a month of owning the Beetle Pro, I finally dropped my Fold. I fumbled it in my hands as I was unfolding the phone while walking. It went flying out in front of me and landed on a hard, ceramic tile floor. There was not a scratch on the case and no damage to the phone! Also, I highly recommend the "Milomdoi for Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 5G Screen Protector [3 Pack Inside and 3 Pack Front] with 3 Pack Tempered Glass Camera Lens Protector with Mounting Positioner Accessories" for protecting the inner screen and camera lenses. The combination of the Supcase and the Milomdoi systems offers a superb level of protection for such an expensive phone. After a month, the Beetle Pro continues to impress me, but not nearly as much as the Fold 4 itself!**SECOND UPDATE** After using the case a few months, I've noticed that the two plastic protrusions that lock the stand into the open position are wearing down. This causes the stand to collapse more easily if the phone is touched too hard when you have it supported by the stand. I'm not certain if there is a solution for this. This is the sole reason that I've changed my rating from a five to a four.**THIRD UPDATE** I did not notice that my phone fell out of my coat pocket onto the garage floor when I was moving cars around. I couldn't find my phone in my pocket when I was done. I finally found it, and it was under the left rear tire of my SUV! Fearing the worst, I backed up and retrieved the phone. The case had a couple of scratches on it, but other than that, the phone was undamaged and the case was not broken. So, I guess that it works pretty well for protecting your phone from the weight of a car. I was pretty impressed that that the hinges of my Fold 4 still functioned properly, too.
